Colombia Stock Movers: Bancolombia, Isagen, Pacific Rubiales

-- B y   C a m i l a   R u s s o
-- 
2011-03-30T20:25:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-30/colombia-stock-movers-bancolombia-rises-pacific-rubiales-falls.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4 p.m. New York time.  The IGBC Index fell 0.4 percent to 14,303.74, while the
Colcap Index declined 0.3 percent to 1,703.93.  Bancolombia SA (PFBCOLO)  , the nation’s biggest lender,
rose 1.2 percent to 29,280 pesos.  Fitch Ratings  assigned a BBB-
rating, the lowest investment grade, to Bancolombia’s holding
company Grupo de Inversiones Suramericana SA.  Isagen SA (ISAGEN CB) dropped 1.2 percent to 2,400 pesos.
The Colombian state-controlled power producer said its
shareholders approved plans to issue shares abroad, according to
a regulatory filing late yesterday.  Pacific Rubiales Energy Corp. (PRE)  , the Toronto-based
 oil company  with fields in  Colombia , slid 2 percent to 49,580
pesos, the lowest since Sept. 29. Crude oil fell 0.5 percent to
$104.30 per barrel after a U.S. government report showed a
larger-than-forecast gain in supplies.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Camila Russo in New York at 
 crusso15@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
